.TH TIX\-NOTE 1 "February 2026" "tix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tix\-note \- manage notes in the tix ticket system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tix note add
.I "text"
.br
.B tix note list
.br
.B tix note done
.I id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Notes are ephemeral information stored alongside tasks and issues.
They are useful for recording decisions, context, or observations
that don't warrant a task or issue.
.PP
Note IDs use the prefix
.BR N\- .
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS tix note add \fI"text"\fR
Create a new note.
The text must be non\-empty.
The author is auto\-filled from
.BR "git config user.name" .
.PP
.B Output:
.RS
.nf
{"id":"N\-XXXXXXXX","text":"..."}
.fi
.RE
.SS tix note list
List all pending notes as a JSON array.
.PP
.B Output:
.RS
.nf
[{"id":"N\-XXXXXXXX","type":2,"status":0,"name":"..."},...]
.fi
.RE
.SS tix note done \fIid\fR
Archive a note (delete it from active state).
.PP
.B Output:
.RS
.nf
{"id":"N\-XXXXXXXX","status":"archived"}
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Command succeeded.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid arguments.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tix (1)
